M a l e: Protarsomeres 1 to 3 slightly widened. Aedeagus (
Figs 65-68
) 0.63-0.70 mm long, symmetrical. Median lobe with large, oval, fairly sclerotized basal bulb. Apical process very short, bent ventrally, with broad apical ostium. Articular process large, prominent ventrally. Parameres broad, sclerotized in basal section and at dorsal edges, with large membranous lobes very densely strigulate. Internal sac with large, elongate basal sclerites, elongate tuft of denticles and flattened flagellum extruded in repos.
